    "gpuDriver": "NVIDIA 390.116",
    "kernel": "4.15.0-48-generic",
    "notes": "I'd say that for any casual player this is very good. There are still some issues though that affect everyone who wants to play levels which are harder than medium demon.\nPreviously I had a problem which made the game lag a lot with vsync off. This has now been fixed although the problem still seems to exist with Wine. (This is a big problem for hard levels since vsync seems to cause input lag and it doesn't let you take advantage of the 144hz physics bug which makes flying a little bit easier)\n-For some reason with vsync on there seem to be problems especially with the wave. I think this is likely due to input lag and turning vsync off helps a little bit.\n-That brings me to my second problem which is input lag. I have a 144hz screen and the input lag seems to be even greater than on my phone. It might be because of my out of date drivers and I'll update them to test if it works better after that. Wine on the other hand doesn't seem to have almost any input lag. I haven't used Windows in a long time but I think it's comparable to it.\n-The second biggest problem for me is that the game is locked to 60hz no matter what. Wine seems to automatically use the maximum refresh rate of the screen when the game is fullscreen. \n\nTo sum things up:\nWine is almost perfect but the lag and jittering that occurs with vsync off is a big problem. Proton on the other hand doesn't have that issue but it's capped to 60hz and has huge input lag.",
    "os": "Linux Mint 19.1 Tessa",
    "protonVersion": "Default",
    "ram": "8 GB",
    "rating": "Silver",
